<!-- MainCellStart --><TD VALIGN='TOP'><CENTER><table border=0 cellpadding=5 bgcolor=#DDDDDD width=50% background='/images/table-head-bg.jpg'><tr><td background=''><table border=0 cellpadding=5 bgcolor=#BB0000 width=100%><tr><td width=50% background='/images/table-bg.jpg'><b><font size=+3 color=#FFF000><center>EverTools News<center></font></b></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></center><HR SIZE=1 WIDTH=80%></CENTER><BR><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Saturday, April 7th, 2001</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>11:41am - EverLogs File Problem...</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
We are aware of a problem that EverLogs is currently having in which it reports a file is missing.  This is due to the fact that one of the files (template.htm) had to be renamed at the last minute (template.txt) in order to work with our new udpate servers correctly.  An updated version of EverLogs using the new file should be posted later today.
<BR><BR><B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Friday, April 6th, 2001</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>3:34pm - EverTools Release 7 posted</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
Release 7 is now posted, and avalible on the download page.  Everyone will need to manually download either the full or update versions.  Please let me know if you have any problems with them.
<BR><BR><B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>10:14am - EverTools Release 7 info</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
Over the last few days I have been working on a new and improved version of the auto-updater.  I've been putting this off for over a year now, and with the recent network problems, there is not a better time than now to get this done.
<P>The Drawback to this is that it will require everyone to download a new version of EverTools, or atleast a new version of the auto-updater utility and control center.  This will hopefully be avalible later today.  Betwen now and then, when you update the current version, you will get a message saying it is out of date.
<BR><BR><B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Tuesday, April 3rd, 2001</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>2:26pm - Re-evaluating</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
I'm currently in the process of re-evaluating the future and direction of EverTools.  Over the last year the various evertool projects have been neglected greatly.  Due to the update issues we have had over the last few days.  I'm working on deciding what the future will bring for EverTools.  I'm sorry for any problems this may cause any of the current users, and I greatly appreaciate all the support I have recieved over the last two years.
